headline: Realtor.com®: Renters Now Spend Less than a Quarter of Their Income on Rent
summary: Rents declined again in September, according to the Realtor.com® September Rent Report, extending a two-year stretch of easing prices and modestly improving affordability for typical households. The latest drop, the second month-over-month decline since March, reflects the market's normal cooling heading into fall.

headline: Does the Murdoch TikTok Buzz Change the Value Story for News Shares?
summary: If you’re holding shares of News, or simply watching from the sidelines and wondering what to do next, you’ve probably noticed that the ride hasn’t exactly been smooth lately. The stock just closed at $26.09, dipping 7.0% over the past week and down 10.7% for the past month. Zoom out a little, though, and the longer-term chart looks more promising.
